\shape smallcaps
lemma 1: 
\shape default
\emph on
Fix any 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi_{1}>0$
\end_inset

 and let 
\begin_inset Formula $x^{1*}$
\end_inset

 satisfy
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\mathbb{P}\left(x^{1}+x^{2}\leq y^{*}\vert x^{1}=x^{1*}\right)\underline{\omega}\qquad\\
+\left[1-\mathbb{P}\left(x^{1}+x^{2}\leq y^{*}\vert x^{1}=x^{1*}\right)\right]\overline{\omega} & =1/\eta,
\end{align*}

\end_inset

or 
\begin_inset Formula $x^{1*}=0$
\end_inset

 if that equation has no solution.
 Then the rule 
\begin_inset Formula $R_{1}$
\end_inset

 defined by threshold 
\begin_inset Formula $x^{1*}$
\end_inset

 is uniquely optimal within the class of rules that condition only on 
\begin_inset Formula $x^{1}$
\end_inset

.
\emph default

\begin_inset VSpace bigskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Equate marginal benefits (
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{P}$
\end_inset

 more poor people and 
\begin_inset Formula $1-\mathbb{P}$
\end_inset

 more rich people get the transfer) with the marginal cost 
\begin_inset Formula $1/\eta$
\end_inset

.
\begin_inset VSpace bigskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
..Even when there are agency issues.
\end_layout

