\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Is it always the case that having stronger enforcement increases welfare?
 No!
\begin_inset VSpace bigskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\shape smallcaps
proposition 3: 
\shape default
\emph on
Let the probability of detecting a violation be constant (
\begin_inset Formula $\pi\left(a_{i},\mathbf{x}_{i},R\right)=\pi>0$
\end_inset

 whenever 
\begin_inset Formula $a_{i}\neq\mathbf{1}\left\{ \mathbf{x}_{i}\in R\right\} $
\end_inset

), If 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

 perfectly targets the poor, then 
\begin_inset Formula $\partial V/\partial f\geq0$
\end_inset

.
 If 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

 does not perfectly target the poor, so that there are some ineligible poor
 and some eligible rich, then there exist a scalar 
\begin_inset Formula $f^{*}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\underline{\alpha}^{*}\left(f\right)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\overline{\alpha}^{*}\left(f\right)$
\end_inset

 such that if 
\begin_inset Formula $f>f^{*}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\underline{\alpha}>\underline{\alpha}^{*}\left(f\right)$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $\overline{\alpha}<\overline{\alpha}^{*}\left(f\right)$
\end_inset

 then 
\begin_inset Formula $\partial V/\partial f<0$
\end_inset

.
\emph default

\begin_inset VSpace bigskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Intuition: 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
If you have a perfect rule, you want to force the official to use it
\begin_inset VSpace medskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If you have an imperfect rule, then how much you want to force the official
 to use it depends on how much you disagree about who is deserving.
\begin_inset VSpace medskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If sufficiently aligned: 
\begin_inset Formula $\underline{\alpha}$
\end_inset

 is large, and 
\begin_inset Formula $\overline{\alpha}$
\end_inset

 is small, then let the official use his discretion to violate your rule
 sometimes.
\end_layout

