\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Chetty et al (2013): Empirical Strategy
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Can we use cities with no bunching as a counterfactual for cities with bunching?
\begin_inset VSpace bigskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\shape smallcaps
assumption 2A
\shape default
 (Cross-Sectional Identification): 
\emph on
Individuals’ skills do not vary across cities with different levels of knowledge
 about the tax credit:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
G\left(\alpha_{i}\vert\lambda_{c}\right)=G\left(\alpha_{i}\right)\:\forall\lambda_{c}
\]

\end_inset


\emph default

\begin_inset VSpace bigskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Now we can compare cities with and without bunching:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\hat{\Delta F}=F\left(z\vert\boldsymbol{\tau}\right)-F\left(z\vert\boldsymbol{\tau},\phi_{c}=0\right)
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Chetty et al (2013): Empirical Strategy
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Assumption 2A is strong (why?)
\begin_inset VSpace bigskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
We can relax it by studying earnings changes when people become eligible
 for EITC.
 Here, use birth of first child which makes people eligible for EITC.
\begin_inset VSpace bigskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\shape smallcaps
assumption 2B
\shape default
 (Panel Identification): 
\emph on
Changes in skills when an individual becomes eligible for the credit do
 not vary across cities with different levels of knowledge about the tax
 credit:
\emph default
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
G_{t}\left(\alpha_{i}\vert\lambda_{c}\right)-G_{t-1}\left(\alpha_{i}\vert\lambda_{c}\right)=G_{t}\left(\alpha_{i}\right)-G_{t-1}\left(\alpha_{i}\right)\,\forall\lambda_{c}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Under this assumption we can construct a difference in differences estimator:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\hat{\Delta F}_{DD} & =\left[F_{t}\left(z\vert\boldsymbol{\tau}\right)-F_{t}\left(z\vert\boldsymbol{\tau},\phi_{c}=0\right)\right]\\
 & \quad-\left[F_{t-1}\left(z\vert\boldsymbol{\tau}\right)-F_{t-1}\left(z\vert\boldsymbol{\tau},\phi_{c}=0\right)\right]
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

