\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
How effective are proxy means tests (PMT) in practice in a developing country?
\begin_inset VSpace medskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
In particular, do communities know more than the proxies and can that be
 leveraged to improve targeting?
\begin_inset VSpace medskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
What is the tradeoff? 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Communities have better information.
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Assets capture permanent income.
 Wouldn't observe severe negative shocks.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Poor PMT seen as illegitimate by community.
 
\begin_inset VSpace medskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Communities may disagree with government
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
May perceive poverty differently
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
May favor friends/relatives of elites
