T1
\end_layout

\end_inset


\emph on
PMT
\emph default
.
 Government used 49 indicators (home attributes, assets, hh composition,
 education, occupation etc) and a regression to create poverty scores.
 Enumerators collect this data and generate poverty scores.
 Lowest scores got the transfer.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
T2
\end_layout

\end_inset


\emph on
Community Targeting.

\emph default
 Facilitator holds community meeting.
 List all households in the village and go through them one by one to rank
 them by poverty.
 After ranking finalized, quota of beneficiaries revealed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
T3
\end_layout

\end_inset


\emph on
Hybrid.

\emph default
 Do the community ranking.
 Then 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

verify
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 1.5 
\begin_inset Formula $\times$
\end_inset

 quota using PMT scores.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Community subtreatments:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Elite capture: Either whole community or only elite invited to the meeting
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Randomize the order in which households are ranked to test for effort effects
 (fatigue).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Preferences: Some meetings in the day (more women) others in the evening
 (more men), others place high emphasis on poverty.
\end_layout

