\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Study a large transfer program in Indonesia: Program Keluarga Harapan (PKH)
\begin_inset VSpace medskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Targeted at households with consumption/capita < 80% of poverty line, and
 with pregnant woman/children 0-5/children with <9 years of schooling.
\begin_inset VSpace medskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Recipients get $67–$250/year (3.5–13% of avg consumption)
\begin_inset VSpace medskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
2.4 million households enrolled in 2013.
\begin_inset VSpace medskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Targeting is hard: per-capita consumption is hard to observe.
\begin_inset VSpace medskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The government does a PMT.
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Every 3 years, stats bureau does a nationwide survey.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Potentially eligible households + local leaders' recommendations surveyed.
 Asked 30 questions.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Supplemented with location-level data
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Generate district-level formula for predicting consumption.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_deeper
